---
title: Pancetta White Pizzas with Baby Broccoli, Ricotta, and Herbs de Provence
description: White pizzas don’t get the credit they deserve. Just because they’re not coated in a heavy layer of tomatoes doesn’t mean that they’re lacking in flavor. In fact, in our version, going sauceless means that all of the attention is brought to the toppings. Here, that’s snappy baby broccoli, salty bursts of pancetta, and a garlic and herb-accented spread of ricotta cheese. We’re not going to argue with that.
